 thing as a “normal” menstrual cycle. In fact, menstrual cycles are incredibly variable and highly responsive to environmental and psychological stressors. Clancy takes up a host of timely issues surrounding menstruation, from bodily autonomy, menstrual hygiene, and the COVID-19 vaccine to the ways racism, sexism, and medical betrayal warp public perceptions of menstruation and erase it from public life.Offering a revelatory new perspective on one of the most captivating biological processes in the human body, Period will change the way you think about the past, present, and future of periods.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh  aDarwin's finches.  aEl Niño.  aGalápagos.  aThe Beak of the Finch.  aU.K. background.  aautobiography.  abehavior.  acollaborates with wife.  aecology.  aevolution.  afootsteps of Charles Darwin.  agenetics.  aglobal travel.  ainternational prizes.  along-term research.  anaturalist.  aspecies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074974840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691246826?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691246826423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691246826/original  a978-3-11-074974-8  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK